&lt;p&gt;As Product Manager, you will own the vision, strategy, and roadmap for one of Coast’s non-fuel spend products; expanding our platform beyond fuel into the broader universe of operational expenses, including expense management, accounts payable, reimbursements, and vendor payments. You will lead a cross-functional team of engineers and designers to build products that help fleet and field-based businesses move more of their day-to-day spend onto Coast in a way that is simpler, safer, and more trusted than existing solutions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who is comfortable operating in ambiguity, curious about complex financial workflows, and motivated by turning messy, real-world problems into simple, intuitive products. You should be equally comfortable thinking at a systems level and getting hands-on, whether that’s pressure-testing a concept, prototyping a flow, or working closely with engineering to translate constraints into thoughtful product decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this role will require you to be comfortable with working in-person at our NYC office at least 3.5 days/week on average.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
